Create Messaging Users

Salesforce automatically creates messaging user records for customers when they message your company. However, depending on your business needs, you may want to use additional methods to mass-create or automate the creation of messaging user records.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience.
This article applies to: Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, and standard and enhanced SMS channels.
Create Messaging Users with Imported Data

Import a CSV file of user data into Salesforce using Data Loader. This lets you add new messaging user records to your org without them messaging you first.

To import data:

Find the Messaging Channel ID from Setup > Messaging Settings.
Populate a CSV file with customer information, including phone number or Facebook page ID.
Exclude hyphens, parentheses, and spaces.
Use a +1 in front of phone numbers.
Add the Messaging Channel ID and consent status to the CSV file.
Import the CSV file into Salesforce using Data Loader.

Agents can only initiate enhanced messaging sessions with a customer if they have a messaging user record linked to the desired channel. Messaging user records are created automatically when customers first message you, though you can create or import them manually if you already gathered your customerâ€™s messaging consent elsewhere.

Create Messaging Users with Process Builder

Use Process Builder to automate the creation of messaging user records. This ensures that messaging user records are created automatically based on data in other Salesforce records.

To use Process Builder:

Include a command to create a messaging user record using field values.
Ensure that the process completes at least the minimum fields required to create a messaging user record: MessageType, MessagingChannel, MessagingConsentStatus, MessagingPlatformKey, and IsoCountryCode.
title: Creating Messaging Users in Salesforce
